{{globalStreamThread}} in {{KafkaStreams}} class ignores all exceptions and fails to apply the user-provided {{StreamsUncaughtExceptionHandler}} in:
{code:java}
public void setUncaughtExceptionHandler(final StreamsUncaughtExceptionHandler userStreamsUncaughtExceptionHandler)
{code}
This can lead to streams being stuck in faulty state after an exception is thrown during their initialization phase (e.g. failure to load the RocksDB native library). The exception isn't logged, so debugging such problem is difficult.

From my understanding of the {{b62d8b97}} commit message, the following code is unnecessary as the {{globalStreamThread}} can't be replaced and the issue description from KAFKA-12699 doesn't apply to it. Removing it should help.
{code:java}
if (globalStreamThread != null) {
    globalStreamThread.setUncaughtExceptionHandler((t, e) -> { }
    );
}
{code}

